Samples are digested with pancreatic alpha-amylase and amyloglucosidase with incubation conditions similar to AOAC 2017.16 for dietary fiber (McCleary et al., 2002) to remove digestible starch, recovery of the non-digestible (resistant) starch, hydrolysis of the resistant starch with 1.7N sodium hydroxide, then quantitation of D-glucose using a spectrophotometric assay, with resistant starch calculated from measured glucose, using the Megazyme (Neogen®) Rapid Resistant Starch kit (K-RAPRS).
nutrientAnalysisDetails.labMethodLink: Measurement of Resistant Starch by Enzymatic Digestion in Starch and Selected Plant Materials: Collaborative Study
